<paragraph id="1A1E1A5DFF92FF83B6B7FD9BA52BFD12" blockId="4.[170,1229,591,810]" pageId="4" pageNumber="239">
Diagnosis. This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="DDA161DEFF92FF83B4DEFD84A731FDB1" baseAuthorityName="Rossi" baseAuthorityYear="1790" box="[694,836,591,617]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Perithous" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="239" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="divinator">
<emphasis id="28D5C64FFF92FF83B4DEFD84A731FDB1" box="[694,836,591,617]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="239">P. divinator</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but has more abundant yellow coloration of mesosoma: stripes on mesoscutum, scutellum apically, wide arch on propodeum, large spot on hind coxa; and a longer ovipositor (about 4 × length of hind tibia) (
<figureCitation id="829A06D8FF92FF83B69FFD7BA541FD12" box="[247,308,687,714]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[166,199,1766,1788]" captionTargetBox="[272,1126,1043,1744]" captionTargetId="figure-372@4.[272,1126,1043,1744]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 2. Perithous spp.: 1 — P. speculator, female, habitus, lateral view; 2 — P. scurra, female, dorsal view of the second metasomal tergite; 3–4 — dorsal view of propodeum and metasomal tergites I–II, female: 3 — P. divinator; 4 — P. septemcinctorius; 5 — P. scurra, male, habitus, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6454728" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6454728/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="239">fig. 2</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="829A06D8FF92FF83B728FD7BA53BFD11" box="[320,334,687,713]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[170,203,1707,1729]" captionTargetBox="[305,1093,562,1688]" captionTargetId="figure-12@2.[305,1093,558,1689]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig.1.Delomerista spp.1–2 —habitus,lateralview:1—D.cf.japonica, female;2 — D.novita,male;3 —D. novita, female, dorsal view of propodeum; 4, 5 — dorsal view of the second metasomal tergite: 4 — D. pfankuchi, male; 5 — D. novita, female; 6–10 — lateral view of ovipositor tip: 6 — D. pfankuchi; 7 — D. borealis; 8 — D. mandibularis; 9 — D.cf. japonica; 10 — D.japonica (non-Carpathian material); 11–12 — lateral view of two basal antennal segments: 11 — D. borealis; 12 — D. mandibularis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6454726" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6454726/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="239">
<emphasis id="28D5C64FFF92FF83B728FD7BA53BFD11" box="[320,334,687,713]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="239">1</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1A1E1A5DFF92FF83B6B7FD1BA6D7FD32" blockId="4.[170,1229,591,810]" box="[223,674,719,746]" pageId="4" pageNumber="239">Flight period in Carpathians. October.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1A1E1A5DFF92FF83B6B7FD3BA7B3FCF2" blockId="4.[170,1229,591,810]" pageId="4" pageNumber="239">
Remarks. Coloration of metasomal tergites varies from entirely black (with yellowish band posteriorly) to tricolor (
<typeStatus id="C51AA4FFFF92FF83B46AFCDBA618FCF2" box="[514,621,783,810]" pageId="4" pageNumber="239">holotype</typeStatus>
) (see 
<bibRefCitation id="7E3067ACFF92FF83B4D9FCDBA7CCFCF2" author="Taeger, A. &amp; Haupt, H." box="[689,953,783,810]" pageId="4" pageNumber="239" refId="ref3850" refString="Taeger, A., Haupt, H. 2013. Perithous speculator Haupt, 1954, holotype - original description and figures. figshare. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.6084 / m 9. figshare. 867656." type="book" year="2013">Taeger &amp; Haupt, 2013</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
